71.6	Primo_Levi	Primo Levi	Primo Michele Levi was an Italian Jewish chemist and writer. He was the author of two novels and several collections of short stories, essays, and poems. His best-known works include If This Is a Man (1947), his account of the year he spent as a prisoner in the Auschwitz concentration camp in Nazi-occupied Poland; and The Periodic Table (1975) which the Royal Institution of Great Britain named the best science book ever written. He was an atheist.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/7/7e/Primo_Levi.gif/200px-Primo_Levi.gif
